# .easignore — files excluded from the EAS Build project archive.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: in a monorepo, EAS uploads the whole workspace root,
# not just apps/mobile. Without this, ~15 MB of web-only assets (the adhan
# MP3s + web icons in apps/web/public) ride along on every mobile build.
#
# CRITICAL: once an .easignore exists, EAS uses it INSTEAD of .gitignore.
# So every build artifact / secret normally hidden by .gitignore MUST be
# re-listed below, or it will start getting uploaded.

# ---- Dependencies & build output (mirrors .gitignore) ----
node_modules/
.next/
.turbo/
dist/
out/
build/
coverage/
.cache/
web-build/
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts
expo-env.d.ts

# ---- Secrets / env / signing material (NEVER upload) ----
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision

# ---- Expo / generated native (CNG: EAS regenerates these during prebuild) ----
.expo/
.metro-health-check*
.kotlin/
apps/mobile/android/
apps/mobile/ios/

# ---- Logs / OS / editor cruft ----
*.log
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
.vercel/

# ---- Repo tooling/meta not needed by the build ----
.claude/
.superpowers/
.git/

# ---- THE 21.6 MB CULPRIT: web-only assets the mobile build never uses ----
# 13 MB of adhan MP3s + ~2 MB of web icons/images live here. Mobile bundles
# its own assets under apps/mobile/assets, so none of this is needed.
apps/web/public/

# ---- Docs (not part of the build) ----
docs/
Documentation/
*.md
